2-1
===
This is relatively straightforward. Just do the addition, keeping track of carries. You don't have to store the result, just the carry count.

2-2
===
This game (like many other dynamic programming problems) has the property that in certain regimes one player can force the other into a certain behavior. These regimes partition the game space, so you can determine the winner by identifying the partition.

2-3
===
All positive integers that aren't perfect squares have an even factor count, so they'll be toggled an even number of times. Perfect squares have an odd factor count.
